    leaderNote: "Week 37 is the emotional and spiritual core of Term 3 — handle it with great care and pastoral intentionality. This is the week where the theme of OBEDIENCE, carried through the entire curriculum, reaches its fullest definition: 'not my will, but Thine.' The Jim Elliot story is powerful and well-documented — use his actual journal quotations if possible. The journal prompt is the most personally revelatory in the curriculum: teens who write their Gethsemane prayers honestly are at a place of genuine spiritual breakthrough. Create space for private writing time — at least 10 minutes. The ThinkDeeper question about the Father saying 'no' is important apologetically: teens lose faith over unanswered prayer, and this lesson provides a theological framework (the Father's 'no' to Jesus was an act of love) that reframes the experience. Follow up individually with anyone who writes something particularly raw.",
