      obedienceLink: "The resurrection means that the Jesus who demands your obedience is not a dead teacher whose words survive in a book — He is the living Lord, risen and reigning, who is present with His people by His Spirit. 'Lo, I am with you alway, even unto the end of the world' (Matthew 28:20). Obedience to the risen Lord is not compliance with ancient text — it is responsive living in relationship with a living Person. And the resurrection is the guarantee that the obedience asked of you is asked by One who overcame death, who can bring life out of every dying thing, and who will ultimately raise you to the same resurrection He experienced.",
