    leaderNote: "Week 39 is the triumphant conclusion of Term 3 and the theological high point of the entire curriculum. The resurrection lesson deserves the most time and the most careful preparation. The Frank Morison story is historically documented and intellectually compelling — his book 'Who Moved the Stone?' is still in print and is an excellent resource for teens who want to pursue the historical case further. The apologetic material on hallucination theories is essential for this age group — they will encounter these objections in university. Present the evidence as a legal case, not a devotional exercise. The journal prompt (resurrection from personal 'death' to life) is the term's most hopeful exercise and should produce powerful personal writing. Close Term 3 by connecting forward to Term 4: the resurrection is not the end of the story — it is the beginning of the life we are now called to live.",
